        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 7 at 10:39PM CDT by NWS San Angelo TX</headline>
        <description>At 1038 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Paint Creek, moving southeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Haskell, Stamford, Lake Stamford Marina, and Paint Creek.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
